</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>ACR112:v97#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="ACR112"/><meta name="dc:title" content="ACR &#xA;              112-&#xA;                CHAPTERED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div width="100%" style="text-align:center;"><div id="bill_num_title_chap"><span style="text-align:center;font-weight:bold;font-size:1.1em;font-family:'Times New Roman'; "><b>
                Assembly Concurrent Resolution
              
                        No. 112</b></span></div><div style="text-align:center;padding-top: 1.0em;padding-bottom: 1.2em;" id="chap_num_title_chap"><span style="font-size:1.4em;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;">
                      CHAPTER 7</span></div></div><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> Relative to Deaf Awareness Month.</span></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center">
                  
                  [<span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Filed with
              </span><span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Secretary of State
              </span> <span style="font-size: 13pt">February 25, 2026.
                      </span>]
                </div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">ACR 112, Gallagher.
                          Deaf Awareness Month.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This measure would recognize the month of September 2025 as Deaf Awareness Month in California.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_D2C006D4-D883-4361-B809-5496DBB05935"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The purpose of Deaf Awareness Month, celebrated in September, is to bring visibility and awareness to Deaf issues, people, and culture, emphasizing the positive aspects of deafness, encouraging social inclusion, and raising awareness of the organizations locally, nationally, and globally that support those who are deaf; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_94B9554C-C112-4562-B266-CAF03F2596A7"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Deaf Awareness Month traces its roots to the International Week of the Deaf, established in 1958 by the World Federation of the Deaf, and evolving into a month-long celebration and recognition of the Deaf community in 1997; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_6B7CFB74-165D-4C75-A2AE-6D1B406CF0B8"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Deaf Awareness Month seeks to increase public understanding of Deaf issues, individuals, and culture by highlighting barriers faced by deaf individuals and by promoting inclusivity, accessibility, and communication; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_F2FEE85D-AAB4-4692-8221-55BD4E203FDA"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, According to the World Health Organization, over 466,000,000 individuals worldwide are deaf or hard of hearing; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_D2EE6341-8D22-4628-96F5-34AF0AE8BCBD"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Three million Californians identify as deaf or hard of hearing, and the Deaf community intersects with all ages, ethnicities, backgrounds, and geographies; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_0D228F3E-6214-4AC7-AF46-1622D048557C"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Deaf and hard-of-hearing individuals have made, and continue to make, numerous contributions to the cultural and economic vitality of California and the United States; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_CB3C5AB7-5120-4418-96B1-D188BFC46581"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The celebration of Deaf Awareness Month provides a platform for the Deaf community to express their culture, language, and experiences, while offering an opportunity to participate in, learn about, and appreciate Deaf culture; now, therefore, be it</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_62C869B6-1B2D-41B9-BB70-EF9AD15CC7B0"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Assembly of the State of California, the Senate thereof concurring, That the Legislature recognizes the month of September 2025 as Deaf Awareness Month in California; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_06F96457-CC19-4485-8A04-45B54D163F5F"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Chief Clerk of the Assembly transmit copies of this resolution to the author for appropriate distribution.</div></span></span></div></body></html>
